\f0\b\fs20 \cf4 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Question:
\b0 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2  \'a0Take a question?
\f1\fs24 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240

\f0\b\fs20 \cf5 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 President Obama:
\b0 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2  \'a0You know what, I will take a question. \'a0Go ahead.
\f1\fs24 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240

\f0\b\fs20 \cf4 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Question:
\b0 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2  \'a0Every servicemember who is listening to you today, Mr. President, is wondering, are you going to veto the defense bills that are going to pay me? \'a0What is your latest thinking on that? Because we've heard secondhand through statements of policy that your advisors would threaten a veto. \'a0What\'92s your take, sir? \'a0Would you veto the appropriations bills?
\f1\fs24 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240

\f0\b\fs20 \cf5 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 President Obama:
\b0 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2  \'a0Our men and women are going to get paid. \'a0And if you\'92ll note that I've now been President for six and a half years and we've had some wrangling with Congress in the past -- our servicemembers haven't missed a paycheck.
\f1\fs24 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240

\f0\fs20 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 But what is also important in terms of our budget is making sure that we are not short-changing all the elements of American power that allow us to secure the nation and to project our power around the world. \'a0So what we're not going to do is to accept a budget that short-changes our long-term requirements for new technologies, for readiness. \'a0We're not going to eat our seed corn by devoting too much money on things we don't need now and robbing ourselves of the capacity to make sure that we're prepared for future threats.
\f1\fs24 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \

\f0\fs20 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 I've worked very closely with the Chairman and the members of the Joint Chiefs of Staff to develop a budget that is realistic and that looks out into the future and says this is how we're going to handle any possible contingency. \'a0And we can't do that if we've got a budget that short-changes vital operations and continues to fund things that are not necessary.
\f1\fs24 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \

\f0\fs20 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 We also have to remind ourselves that the reason we have the best military in the world is, first and foremost, because we've got the best troops in history. \'a0But it's also because we've got a strong economy, and we've got a well-educated population. \'a0And we've got an incredible research operation and universities that allow us to create new products that then can be translated into our military superiority around the world. \'a0We short-change those, we're going to be less secure.
\f1\fs24 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \

\f0\fs20 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 So the way we have to look at this budget is to recognize that, A, we can't think short term, we've got to think long term; and B, part of our national security is making sure that we continue to have a strong economy and that we continue to make the investments that we need in things like education and research that are going to be vital for us to be successful long term.
\f1\fs24 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240

\f0\b\fs20 \cf4 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Question:
\b0 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2  \'a0As an Army reservist, I'm curious to know if you have any plans to send any more American troops overseas right now, any additional forces.
\f1\fs24 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240

\f0\b\fs20 \cf5 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 President Obama:
\b0 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2  \'a0There are no current plans to do so. \'a0That's not something that we currently discussed. \'a0I've always said that I'm going to do what\'92s necessary to protect the homeland.
\f1\fs24 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240

\f0\fs20 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 One of the principles that we all agree on, though, and I pressed folks pretty hard because in these conversations with my military advisors I want to make sure I'm getting blunt and unadultered [sic] uncensored advice. \'a0But in every one of the conversations that we've had, the strong consensus is that in order for us to succeed long-term in this fight against ISIL we have to develop local security forces that can sustain progress.
\f1\fs24 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \

\f0\fs20 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 It is not enough for us to simply send in American troops to temporarily set back organizations like ISIL, but to then, as soon as we leave, see that void filled once again with extremists. \'a0It is going to be vital for us to make sure that we are preparing the kinds of local ground forces and security forces with our partners that can not only succeed against ISIL, but then sustain in terms of security and in terms of governance.
\f1\fs24 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \

\f0\fs20 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 Because if we try to do everything ourselves all across the Middle East, all across North Africa, we'll be playing Whack-a-Mole and there will be a whole lot of unintended consequences that ultimately make us less secure.
\f1\fs24 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \

\f0\fs20 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 All right? \'a0Thank you. \'a0I didn\'92t even plan to do this. \'a0You guys got two bonus questions.
\f1\fs24 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
